thermal C1 generation and surface sugar chemistry; the resulting activated threonine thioester enters peptide-like assembly before releasing threonine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_016\", \"rxn_017\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_018\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\", \"mol_023\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Systems-chemistry route with cyanamide-compatible surface chemistry\",\n      \"description\": \"A phosphate-rich cyanosulfidic setting produces cyanamide-compatible chemistry alongside glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde, with threonine still formed through the established triose-to-aminonitrile branch.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_018\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_015\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_015\", \"mol_014\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_007\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_006\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_008\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_015\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_014\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_014\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Threonine", "overall_strategy": "This network synthesizes threonine through literature-grounded, interconnected prebiotic routes centered on three experimentally or theoretically discussed regimes: (i) hydrothermal generation of reduced C1/C2 feedstocks and keto-acid/amino-acid precursors on iron-sulfur minerals, (ii) surface cyanosulfidic photoredox chemistry producing glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde/dihydroxyacetone, and the Strecker precursor 2-amino-3-hydroxybutanenitrile, and (iii) surface prebiotic sugar/thioester chemistry converting tetrose pools into activated threonine thioesters that hydrolyze or transfer into peptide chemistry. The network uses hub molecules HCN, glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde, tetrose pool, and 2-amino-3-hydroxybutanenitrile to create 10 distinct but connected pathways to threonine, while also representing the major literature caveats: thermal instability of threonine at high hydrothermal temperatures, concentration dependence, and unresolved stereochemical control.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", "iupac_name": "molecular hydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "CH2O2", "iupac_name": "methanoic acid", "common_name": "formate/formic acid", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O2/c2-1-3/h1H,(H,2,3)", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "CH2O", "iupac_name": "methanal", "common_name": "formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "CH4N2", 