nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Threonine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network synthesizes threonine through literature-grounded, interconnected prebiotic routes centered on three experimentally or theoretically discussed regimes: (i) hydrothermal generation of reduced C1/C2 feedstocks and keto-acid/amino-acid precursors on iron-sulfur minerals, (ii) surface cyanosulfidic photoredox chemistry producing glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde/dihydroxyacetone, and the Strecker precursor 2-amino-3-hydroxybutanenitrile, and (iii) surface prebiotic sugar/thioester chemistry converting tetrose pools into activated threonine thioesters that hydrolyze or transfer into peptide chemistry. The network uses hub molecules HCN, glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde, tetrose pool, and 2-amino-3-hydroxybutanenitrile to create 10 distinct but connected pathways to threonine, while also representing the major literature caveats: thermal instability of threonine at high hydrothermal temperatures, concentration dependence, and unresolved stereochemical control.\n\nMOLECULES (23 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O2 (formate/formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH4N2 (cyanamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (dihydroxyacetone) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C4H8O4 (erythrose/threose/erythrulose pool) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H6O3 (alpha-ketoaldehyde intermediate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: H3N (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_013: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_014: C4H9NO2S (activated threonine thioester) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H8N2O (threonine